a:17:{s:4:"name";s:12:"Acivir Cream";s:11:"small_descr";s:98:"Acivir Cream is an antiviral medicine used to treat cold sores caused by the herpes simplex virus.";s:14:"small_descr_de";s:0:"";s:14:"small_descr_fr";s:0:"";s:14:"small_descr_es";s:0:"";s:14:"small_descr_it";s:0:"";s:10:"full_descr";s:1234:"<h2 class="DrugOverview__title___1OwgG">Product introduction</h2><p>Cold sores are small painful blisters that may form around the mouth or other areas of the face. This medicine slows down the growth of the virus and promotes the healing of cold sore blisters. <br /><br /></p><h2 class="DrugOverview__title___1OwgG DrugOverview__bottom-padding-sm___3gOgF">Side effects of Acivir Cream</h2><p>Acivir Cream rarely show side effects. However, less commonly, you may experience redness, itching, or burning sensation at the site of application. Consult your doctor if any of these side effects do not resolve with time or worsen. <br /><br />Acivir Cream should be used as prescribed by your doctor. Clean and dry the affected area and apply a thin film of this medicine on it. Wash your hands before and after applying this medicine. Avoid contact with the eyes, mouth, or broken skin. Rinse thoroughly with water in case of accidental contact.<br /><br />Acivir Cream is not recommended if you are allergic to it. Inform your doctor if you are using any other topical medications or skin care products on your face before starting the treatment. Consult your doctor if you are pregnant, planning a pregnancy, or are breastfeeding.</p>";s:13:"full_descr_de";s:0:"";s:13:"full_descr_fr";s:0:"";s:13:"full_descr_es";s:0:"";s:13:"full_descr_it";s:0:"";s:9:"min_price";s:2:"19";s:9:"pack_name";s:5:"tubes";s:4:"type";s:2:"gr";s:7:"analogs";a:4:{s:7:"Valtrex";s:10:"Anti Viral";s:7:"Zovirax";s:10:"Anti Viral";s:12:"Acivir Pills";s:10:"Anti Viral";s:13:"Zovirax Cream";s:10:"Anti Viral";}s:18:"active_ingredients";N;s:8:"packings";a:1:{i:10;a:10:{i:7851;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"7851";s:5:"count";s: